statement.title: Problem Description
statement.content: There are n numbers ${A}_{1},{A}_{2}....{A}_{n}$,your task is to check whether there exists there different positive integers i, j, k ($1\leq i , j , k \leq n$) such that ${A}_{i}-{A}_{j}={A}_{k}$

statement.title: Input
statement.content:
There are multiple test cases, no more than 1000 cases.
First line of each case contains a single integer n.$(3\leq n\leq 100)$.
Next line contains n integers ${A}_{1},{A}_{2}....{A}_{n}$.$(0\leq {A}_{i}\leq 1000)$

statement.title: Output
statement.content: For each case output "YES" in a single line if you find such i, j, k, otherwise output "NO".
